50|$|After {{the death}} of a Soviet leader it was {{customary}} for his successors to open his safe. When <b>Gorbachev</b> <b>had</b> Chernenko's safe opened, it was found to contain a small folder of personal papers and several large bundles of money; a large amount of money was also found in his desk.|$|R
50|$|The year is 1985, and Mikhail <b>Gorbachev</b> <b>has</b> come {{to power}} in the Soviet Union. While his Glasnost and Perestroika reforms are welcomed by western governments, there are {{communist}} hardliners in his own government that are unsympathetic to his cause and are ready {{to do anything to}} stop these reforms.|$|E
