5000|$|Major {{met with}} his cabinet that same day on 19 August {{to deal with the}} crisis. He added, [...] "There seems little doubt that President <b>Gorbachev</b> <b>has</b> been removed from power by an un{{constitutional}} seizure of power. There are constitutional ways of removing the president of the Soviet Union; they have not been used. I believe that the whole world has a very serious stake in the events currently taking place in the Soviet Union. The reform process there is of vital importance to the world and of most vital importance of course to the Soviet people themselves and I hope that is fully clear. There {{is a great deal of}} information we dont yet have, but I would like to make clear above all that we would expect the Soviet Union to respect and honor all the commitments that President <b>Gorbachev</b> <b>has</b> made on its behalf, he said, echoing sentiments from a litany of other Western leaders." ...|$|E
